POTATO LATE BLIGHT: VIDEO AVAILABLE
===================================
[see: Potato late blight: global threat 960617
Potato late blight: global initiative 970117151713]
Date: March 1997
From: American Phytopathological Society <aps@scisoc.org>

A new classroom video is available for instructors who wish to
teach about potato late blight. Published to coincide with the
ongoing commemoration of the 150th anniversary of the Irish
Potato Famine, this 25-minute video presents the importance of
food production in daily life, the "disease pyramid" concept, the
life cycle of a plant pathogenic fungus, and social and political
aspects of food distribution. In the USA, call 1-800-328-7560 to
order. Outside of the USA, contact APS PRESS via e-mail at
aps@scisoc.org or via fax at 1-612-454-0766.
--
American Phytopathological Society
APS New Capsule
aps@scisoc.org
